Shared Qs (frieze)


  1. Question

    There are 7 different Frieze groups. I depicted them below with their IUC names and Conway nicknames.


    For each of the patterns below, determine the Frieze group.

    Pattern 1


    Match the IUC name:

    Pattern 2


    Match the Conway nickname:



    Solution

    • The first pattern is a p2mg (which is also called spinning sidle).
    • The second pattern is a jump (which is also called p11m).
